1. OVERVIEW
1.1 Problem Statement
Live football markets move violently the instant a match state changes. When a goal, red card, penalty, or VAR overturn occurs, every connected market (1X2, Handicap, Total Goals, Correct Score) must reprice simultaneously. If even one quote stays stale for seconds, informed traders drain margin before a human trader can react. Traditional market-making bots either (a) predict direction naively and lose, or (b) quote statically and get picked off during event shocks.

1.2 Solution
RAVEN is an autonomous in-play market maker that earns spread under normal flow, and — the instant a cryptographically verified match event hits — withdraws quotes, neutralizes exposure across connected markets, then safely re-enters. Every quote, hedge, and risk action is anchored on Solana as a verifiable decision receipt.

1.3 Core Value Proposition
"We don't predict the match. We survive it — profitably, and verifiably."

1.4 Success Criteria
Primary: Win 1st place (49.5/50 target on judging rubric).
Product: Demonstrate positive spread P&L under normal flow AND minimized loss during a verified event shock, in a single deterministic replay.
Technical: All 5 judging criteria satisfied simultaneously in one demo.
2. GOALS & NON-GOALS
2.1 Goals
#	Goal
G1	Ingest live/replayed TxLINE odds, scores, and match events in real time
G2	Autonomously quote bid/ask on 3 connected markets and earn spread
G3	Detect verified event shocks and withdraw within milliseconds
G4	Neutralize cross-market exposure via automated hedging
G5	Anchor every critical decision as a verifiable receipt on Solana devnet
G6	Provide deterministic replay so judges can observe the system live
2.2 Non-Goals
#	Non-Goal	Rationale
N1	Real-money betting platform	Out of scope, legal risk, no time
N2	Token / NFT / social features	Dilutes trading focus
N3	LLM as decision-maker	LLM only explains decisions, never trades
N4	Supporting all market types	Depth over breadth; 3 markets only
N5	Full order-book DEX on mainnet	Simulated/devnet execution suffices
N6	Heavy ML training pipeline	Deterministic model beats black box for judges
3. USERS & PERSONAS
Persona	Need	How RAVEN serves
Sportsbook trading desk	Protect margin during live events	Shadow-mode agent that flags/executes withdrawals
Prediction market operator	Keep markets solvent under shocks	Autonomous suspension + hedge
B2B data intermediary	Prove data-driven decisions	On-chain audit trail via receipts
Hackathon judge	Evaluate a real, working trading agent	Deterministic replay + verify.ts
Primary persona for the demo narrative: Sportsbook trading desk running RAVEN in shadow mode.

