FR2.3 Apply event-hazard adjustment based on score, match_time, red cards using inhomogeneous/bivariate Poisson goal intensities.
FR2.4 Constraint: Adjusted probability must not deviate from TxLINE consensus beyond a bounded threshold (model-risk cap).
FR2.5 Do NOT use the term "theta decay"; model is event-hazard based.
Acceptance: Reservation price computed = consensus + state adjustment + inventory + latency/vol premium.
F3 — Quote Engine
FR3.1 Continuously emit {bid, ask, max_size, expiry} per market.
FR3.2 Apply inventory skew: shift quotes against over-held outcome.
FR3.3 Widen spread when: event hazard ↑, feed latency ↑, volatility ↑, inventory imbalance, linked-market incoherence.
FR3.4 Fractional Kelly sets capital-usage cap ONLY (does not generate quotes).
Acceptance: Given fair prob 0.582 → outputs coherent bid/ask (e.g., 0.547 / 0.603) with visible skew and premium components.
F4 — Risk Kernel / State Machine
FR4.1 States: NORMAL → CAUTION → WITHDRAW → HEDGE → RECALIBRATE → REENTER.
FR4.2 On verified critical event: cancel all open quotes, exit affected cluster, hedge exposure, wait for 3 consecutive stable updates, re-quote.
FR4.3 Compute risk score:
risk
=
0.30
 
consensusDev
+
0.25
 
