risk=0.30consensusDev+0.25eventLatency+0.20crossMarketIncoherence+0.15exposure+0.10feedConfidence
Acceptance: State transitions occur autonomously with zero manual input; each transition logged.
F5 — Market Dependency Graph
FR5.1 Represent each market as a node; event-driven relationships as edges.
FR5.2 On event, verify all dependent markets moved in expected direction within acceptable latency.
FR5.3 Flag stale linked markets (e.g., 1X2 updated but Handicap stale).
Acceptance: Graph correctly identifies which markets a goal event should affect and detects lag.
F6 — Self-Hedging Engine
FR6.1 Treat all connected positions as one portfolio.
FR6.2 Compute per-event shock exposure (home goal, away goal, red card, no-more-goal).
FR6.3 Select hedge that minimizes: event-shock loss + inventory concentration + hedge cost, without eliminating spread revenue.
FR6.4 Use concrete cross-market instruments (1X2↔Handicap, 1X2↔Double Chance, goal-shock↔Total Goals).
Acceptance: After hedge, residual exposure materially reduced (demo: +12,480 → +930 USDC).
F7 — Solana Decision Receipts
FR7.1 For each critical decision, write receipt to Solana devnet (memo or Anchor program).
FR7.2 Receipt schema: policyHash, txlineSequence, marketStateHash, inventoryBefore, action, reason, quotesCancelled, hedgeTransactions, inventoryAfter, executionTimestamp.
FR7.3 Provide verify.ts for independent verification by judges.
Acceptance: Judge runs verify.ts, confirms decision was made with claimed data at claimed time.
F8 — Deterministic Replay & Counterfactual Lab
FR8.1 Record TxLINE feeds during hackathon window.
FR8.2 Replay at 1x–1000x with millisecond fidelity; agent reproduces identical decisions deterministically.
FR8.3 Run Baseline MM (static, event-blind) vs RAVEN on same feed.
FR8.4 Output real comparison metrics (never pre-picked showcase numbers).
Acceptance: Judges observe live decision-making during review week despite no live matches.
F9 — Adversarial Flow Detector (P1)
FR9.1 Monitor trade behavior: repeated flow to agent's stale side, one-directional aggression pre-event, abnormal fill concentration.
FR9.2 Response: reduce size → widen spread → shorten quote expiry → withdraw.
F10 — Live Control Room (P1)
FR10.1 All-black terminal + minimal web dashboard.
FR10.2 Panels: live match, odds, score events, agent state, risk score, exposure, autonomous actions, dependency graph.
5. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
ID	Requirement	Target
NFR1	Event-to-withdrawal latency	< 250 ms
NFR2	Determinism	Same input → same output, 100%
NFR3	Judge testability	No token purchase / deposit required
NFR4	Uptime during demo	Replay must run flawlessly
NFR5	Code clarity	Documented, clean, defensible logic
NFR6	Data compliance	No raw TxLINE data redistribution
NFR7	Branding	No FIFA marks / official sponsor imagery
