10. DELIVERABLES (submission checklist)
 Demo video ≤5 min (Loom/YouTube) — hard screening gate
 Public GitHub repo — commit history within hackathon dates
 Deployed link OR working devnet endpoint — judge-testable, no deposit
 Technical documentation — core idea + TxLINE endpoints used
 FEEDBACK.md — latency measurements, schema suggestions, friction (full report)
 verify.ts — independent receipt verification
 New repo, new branding (no legacy project)
 Human-authored architecture explanation (T&C §5.1 — agent-control risk)
 LaTeX-documented formulas in README
 No FIFA marks
11. DEMO SCRIPT (5 min)
Time	Content
0:00–0:25	Problem — "MMs earn until the match changes; one stale quote drains margin."
0:25–0:45	Solution — RAVEN + tagline
0:45–2:20	Normal flow — split screen, spread micro-profits, verified badges
2:20–3:20	Winner moment — penalty event → withdraw → shock exposure → hedge → reopen → receipt (show mechanism, NOT "spread 500%")
3:20–4:20	Counterfactual — Baseline -5,120 vs RAVEN -180, + RAVEN spread P&L +1,460 before event
4:20–5:00	Architecture + B2B — shadow mode + verify.ts live
